                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11 G 93/1205: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-11-16T09:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1921—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 17—12:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Department’s 17, October 27, 1 p.m. Answer to my note of October 29<note
                        n="28" xml:id="d829fn28">See telegram no. 17, Oct. 27, to the Minister in
                        Ecuador, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note> received yesterday states that funds were withdrawn to meet great
                    emergency and that negotiations are in progress which the Government hopes will
                    enable it to replace funds very soon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
